						<summary>

						<p>On a slab built into the wall of the Vēṇugōpālasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1466, Krōdhi, Māgha, śu. 10, Thursday, corresponding to 1545 A.D., January 22.</p>						

						<p>Records the construction of the temple of Gōpīnātha by Koṇḍā-reḍḍi, Koṇḍaya, Kōnayya and Timmaya, for the merit of their family members, belongs to the Sarimāla (Siriyāla)-<hi rend="italic">gōtra.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
